---
import SiteLayout from "../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";
---
<SiteLayout
  title="Homelab & Uses ‚Äî nbdevlab"
  description="Hardware, software, and daily tools powering the nbdevlab homelab."
>
  <section class="projects-shell" aria-labelledby="uses-title">
    <header>
      <h1 id="uses-title">Homelab &amp; uses</h1>
      <p>
        The nbdevlab rack evolves constantly, but these are the staples I rely on to keep experiments resilient and delightful.
        Tap a section to expand the details.
      </p>
    </header>

    <section class="accordion" aria-labelledby="hardware-heading">
      <h2 id="hardware-heading" class="sr-only">Hardware stack</h2>
      <details open>
        <summary>
          <span>Core compute</span>
          <span aria-hidden="true">üñ•Ô∏è</span>
        </summary>
        <div class="accordion__body">
          <p>Dual HP ProLiant DL360 Gen9 nodes with Proxmox VE, Xeon E5-2680v4 CPUs, 128&nbsp;GB ECC RAM, and mirrored NVMe boot.</p>
          <p>GPU passthrough to an RTX 4000 keeps AI workloads local when experiments need low-latency iteration.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>
          <span>Storage &amp; backups</span>
          <span aria-hidden="true">üíæ</span>
        </summary>
        <div class="accordion__body">
          <p>TrueNAS SCALE with 6√ó12&nbsp;TB drives in RAID-Z2 and NVMe cache pool. Nightly replication to Wasabi + quarterly cold
            archive.</p>
          <p>Snapshots stream to an off-site Raspberry Pi cluster for audit trails.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>
          <span>Networking</span>
          <span aria-hidden="true">üåê</span>
        </summary>
        <div class="accordion__body">
          <p>pfSense gateway with dual WAN failover, UniFi aggregation switch, and Wi-Fi 7 AP coverage across the lab.</p>
          <p>All critical services sit behind WireGuard for secure remote access.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
    </section>

    <section class="accordion" aria-labelledby="software-heading">
      <h2 id="software-heading" class="sr-only">Software tooling</h2>
      <details open>
        <summary>
          <span>Observability</span>
          <span aria-hidden="true">üìà</span>
        </summary>
        <div class="accordion__body">
          <p>Grafana, Loki, and Tempo power dashboards and tracing. K6 + Uptime Kuma run synthetic probes with incident webhooks.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>
          <span>Developer workflow</span>
          <span aria-hidden="true">üõ†Ô∏è</span>
        </summary>
        <div class="accordion__body">
          <p>Astro, TypeScript, Cloudflare Pages, and GitHub Actions keep deployment loops quick. Vitest + Playwright cover tests.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>
          <span>Automation</span>
          <span aria-hidden="true">‚ö°</span>
        </summary>
        <div class="accordion__body">
          <p>n8n handles event-driven flows, Ansible patches hosts, and Workers/Queues glue everything together at the edge.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
    </section>

    <section class="card" aria-labelledby="daily-tools-heading">
      <h2 id="daily-tools-heading" class="card__title">Everyday tools</h2>
      <div class="card-grid">
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card__title">Editors &amp; notes</h3>
          <p>VS Code with custom keybindings, Obsidian for lab notes, and Raycast for quick scripts.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card__title">Design</h3>
          <p>Figma for component explorations, Contrast tools to keep WCAG AA honest, and Penpot for quick interactions.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card__title">Collaboration</h3>
          <p>Linear for project threads, Notion for lab documentation, and Slack + Matrix bridges for async sync.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>
  </section>
</SiteLayout>
